etermining the temperature dependence of the solubility data based on the\nabsolute solubility at a certain reference temperature, which we call\n\"solvation funnel\" model. By comparing our results with available experimental\ndata from many sources, we can show that the \"solvation funnel\" model is\nparticularly helpful for providing reliable estimates for the solvation\nbehavior of very light gases, such as hydrogen, where conflicting experimental\ndata exist.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Nov 2015 16:26:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-11"}
