ong the most remarkable\nresults, we have found that at the boundary between the FLP and the F phases a\ngapless mode appears resulting from an accidental symmetry that can be regarded\nas a remanent of a broken $SO(5)$ symmetry. On the other hand, the CAF and PLP\nphases can present dynamical instabilities. We straightforwardly extend the\nprevious results to monolayer graphene.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Nov 2015 02:49:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-12"}
